I remember Rick and Julie and I having a ton of laughs trying to decide what books our characters should be reading when they meet on the train. We decided Jesse should have "All I Need is Love," Klaus Kinski's memoir- it's mind blowingly brilliant & very revealing about the devious nature of Jesse's secret mind. For Celine, "Story of the Eye"- by Georges Bataille- if you know that book- you know Jesse is outmatched.

Richard Easton passed. I first worked with him when he played "Casanova" in Tennessee William's CAMINO REAL (with the magnificent Blair Brown). He was a great actor and mentor to me. He knew everything. "One lifetime is not enough to learn what our profession has to teach us." Later we did Henry IV, The Coast of Utopia, The Cherry Orchard, The Winter's Tale and MacBeth. He stole every show. I am so grateful for his friendship and guidance. His obituary is in my bio if you want to read.

This photo was taken by our Prop Master, John Bert, on the set of The Good Lord Bird, which will air on @Showtime in 2020. We have been shooting our limited series, based on the National Book Award winning novel by James McBride, down here in Virginia for months. John Bert and the whole prop department make John Brown's maps, load his guns, help me keep his prayer journal and help create our whole world. It's hard to take people back 160 years. 
This story is at the heart of America's pain and McBride tells it with wit, laughter, silliness, love, anger and all things human. It's the best role I've ever had, bar none.
